The paper also involves simulation-based analysis, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between different routing strategies, which involves optimization and decision-making, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves statistical analysis of simulation results, which involves the use of machine learning and statistical methods, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the performance evaluation of a system, which involves control and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
